    "body": "> @Haroenv If you refine an item in a RefinementList, it calls the `events` endpoint twice:\r\n> \r\n>     * RefinementList: filter clicked\r\n> \r\n>     * Hits: viewed\r\n> \r\n> \r\n> My point was that we should (at some point) batch these two in a single network request.\r\n\r\n@francoischalifour I missed your feedback before.\r\n\r\n(1) When a page is rendered, `view` event will be sent from hits/infiniteHits.\r\n(2) And when user clicks on refinementList, then `click` will be sent.\r\n\r\nThere should be a time gap between (1) and (2).\r\n(1) is programmatic and (2) is triggered by user action.\r\n\r\nIf there are a bunch of events sent programmatically, then we could batch them in a bucket of 1 second or something like that. For example, if a user has multiple hits or infiniteHits widgets on a single page, then multiple `view` events could be sent.\r\n\r\nLet me know what you think. We can improve this later including more opinions :) ",
